THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, liability may be established
4 for a discriminatory housing practice if:
5 (a) The practice was motivated by a discriminatory intent; or
6 (b) Except as otherwise provided in this section, the practice was not
7 motivated by a discriminatory intent but the practice actually or predictably
8 results in a [disparate impact] discriminatory effect on a group of persons or
9 creates, increases, reinforces or perpetuates segregated housing patterns because
10 of race, religious creed, color, national origin, disability, sexual orientation,
11 gender identity or expression, ancestry, familial status or sex.
12 2. There is no liability for a discriminatory housing practice pursuant to
13 paragraph (b) of subsection 1 if, based on evidence that is not hypothetical or
14 speculative:
15 (a) The practice is necessary to achieve one or more substantial, legitimate
16 and nondiscriminatory interests of the respondent; and
17 (b) The interests of the respondent described in paragraph (a) could not be
18 served by another practice that has a less discriminatory effect.
19 3. For purposes of paragraph (b) of subsection 1, the complainant must
20 establish that a challenged practice caused or predictably will cause a [disparate
21 impact.] discriminatory effect. If the complainant meets such burden of proof, the
22 respondent has the burden of proving that the challenged practice is necessary to
23 achieve one or more substantial, legitimate and nondiscriminatory interests of the
24 respondent. If the respondent meets his or her burden of proof, the complainant
25 may still prevail upon proving that the substantial, legitimate and
26 nondiscriminatory interests supporting the challenged practice could be served by
27 another practice that has a less discriminatory effect.
28 4. As used in this section:
29 (a) “Complainant” means a person by whom, or on whose behalf:
30 (1) A complaint is filed with the Commission pursuant to NRS 118.110;
31 or
32 (2) An action is commenced pursuant to NRS 118.120.
33 (b) “Respondent” means a person against whom:
34 (1) A complaint is filed with the Commission pursuant to NRS 118.110;
35 or
36 (2) An action is commenced pursuant to NRS 118.120.

